WEBVTT

00:07.091 --> 00:08.877
[DIGGING]

00:16.475 --> 00:17.726
[GASPS]

00:22.440 --> 00:23.646
You're still here.

00:23.858 --> 00:26.941
Thought maybe you could use
a ride to the Bellefleurs'.

00:27.361 --> 00:30.524
I'm thinking I might need
to take a little walk first.

00:32.408 --> 00:34.899
Well, I could wait here for you.

00:36.954 --> 00:38.990
Or you could join?

00:39.707 --> 00:41.493
Or I could do that.

00:48.299 --> 00:49.664
That was a beautiful ceremony.

00:49.842 --> 00:53.209
-| just wish Jason could've been there.
-Yeah, I know you do.

00:53.387 --> 00:54.923
I know you're worried about him.

00:55.097 --> 00:58.225
Some guys, you meet them...

00:58.392 --> 01:00.883
...and you just know
they're always gonna be okay.

01:01.062 --> 01:04.350
Survivors.
Jason's one of those guys.

01:04.523 --> 01:05.683
You know that, right?

01:05.858 --> 01:09.692
To be honest, Alcide,
I'm not sure I know anything anymore.

01:10.363 --> 01:13.947
I'm starting to feel like there's
no rhyme or reason left in this world.

01:14.158 --> 01:17.821
Well, that's what death does, rips
the ground right out from under your feet...

01:17.995 --> 01:19.860
...makes you wonder
if it was there to begin with.

01:20.039 --> 01:22.371
But it was. lt'll come back.

01:22.583 --> 01:23.914
Heh.

01:24.919 --> 01:26.125
What?

01:27.546 --> 01:29.411
You lay cement.

01:29.882 --> 01:30.917
Yeah?

01:31.092 --> 01:33.583
Well, don't take this
the wrong way...

01:33.761 --> 01:35.126
...but you surprise me is all.

01:35.930 --> 01:37.340
And being what I am...

01:37.515 --> 01:40.473
...not too many people
can sneak up on me like that.

01:43.271 --> 01:45.978
That comment you made
at the funeral...

01:46.148 --> 01:47.934
...about was I a telepath
or something?

01:48.109 --> 01:49.394
Yeah?

01:49.568 --> 01:51.308
Sometimes I wish I was...

01:54.615 --> 01:56.571
...tell what you were thinking.

01:57.159 --> 02:00.071
Believe me, my head's
the last place you'd wanna be.

02:01.289 --> 02:02.574
That ain't true.

02:05.710 --> 02:07.075
[ALCIDE SNIFFING]

02:07.295 --> 02:09.001
What is it?

02:10.506 --> 02:12.462
It's vamps.

02:12.675 --> 02:14.506
[VAMPIRES CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

02:20.057 --> 02:21.672
What the fuck?

02:23.853 --> 02:25.639
[LAUGHING]

02:30.901 --> 02:32.607
Oh, my God.

02:39.827 --> 02:41.192
ALCIDE:
How's this even possible?

02:42.538 --> 02:44.449
Bill was right about everything.

02:49.128 --> 02:52.620
Hey, have at it, y'all.
Bring the inside outside.

02:52.798 --> 02:54.129
The house is yours!

02:57.636 --> 02:59.217
[SIGHS]

03:00.931 --> 03:02.671
ALCIDE:
At least Jason's okay.

03:03.017 --> 03:04.803
-l have to go.
-l'm coming with you.

03:04.977 --> 03:07.138
-You don't have to.
-There's a pack of daywalking vamps.

03:07.313 --> 03:09.429
It's not what you think. I'm safe.

03:09.607 --> 03:11.598
-Sookie.
-Alcide.

03:13.486 --> 03:15.226
I'm a survivor too.

05:12.188 --> 05:13.223
WOMAN:
Burn them!

05:13.397 --> 05:15.638
Burn the fucking prison clothes!

05:24.617 --> 05:27.450
JONATHAN: We need croquet!
WOMAN 2: And volleyball!

05:27.620 --> 05:29.611
MAN: Yeah!
-Who's making a Target run?

05:29.788 --> 05:32.621
MAN: Hell, yeah! I'll go!
-Yeah.

05:33.083 --> 05:34.584
MAN:
Come on!

05:37.421 --> 05:38.877
All right...

05:39.798 --> 05:42.665
...remember how you said
the day was gonna come...

05:42.843 --> 05:45.926
...when l was gonna want
to have sex with you?

05:47.306 --> 05:49.763
What if that day has already come?

05:50.267 --> 05:52.303
Not yet, Jason.

05:53.062 --> 05:54.097
VVhen?

05:54.271 --> 05:57.138
Little by little, we'll get there.

05:58.234 --> 05:59.940
I know, but--

06:00.861 --> 06:02.146
I'm offering you my blood.

06:02.321 --> 06:04.403
-Yeah, but--
-Take it.

06:04.573 --> 06:06.154
Okay.

06:07.660 --> 06:08.866
SOOKIE: Jason.
JASON: Yeah?

06:09.578 --> 06:10.818
Hey, Sook.

06:10.996 --> 06:13.578
-Who the fuck is she?
-Whoa, whoa. It's my sister.

06:13.749 --> 06:16.081
You never mentioned anything
about having a sister.

06:16.252 --> 06:19.164
-What's going on here?
-Violet, I swear it to you. She's--

06:19.338 --> 06:20.828
Sook, tell her you're my sister.

06:21.006 --> 06:22.212
-Tell her.
-Are you?

06:22.383 --> 06:25.841
-Yes, I'm his sister. What the fuck?
-Fuck.

06:29.723 --> 06:33.511
Then you are my sister too.

06:37.064 --> 06:39.271
Sook, meet Violet.

06:39.441 --> 06:41.352
She's European.

06:43.237 --> 06:46.650
Well, I'm sure you two probably have
a lot of catching up to do.

06:47.157 --> 06:48.772
I'll let you be.

06:50.869 --> 06:52.609
I'm hers now.

06:52.788 --> 06:54.744
-Are you okay?
JASON: Yeah.

06:55.291 --> 07:00.206
It's fucking weird, but, Sook, I think | feel
how you felt way back with Bill...

07:00.379 --> 07:02.540
...like someone has my back.

07:02.715 --> 07:05.752
Be careful. When your heart
runs away with you...

07:05.926 --> 07:08.918
...it's easy to believe that someone
will have your back forever.

07:10.139 --> 07:14.223
But I'm learning that forever's
a rare thing in this world...

07:14.393 --> 07:16.509
...no matter what vampires say.

07:17.271 --> 07:18.886
Sook, are you okay?

07:19.064 --> 07:20.395
Yeah.

07:20.566 --> 07:23.182
-l'm gonna be fine.
-You promise, now?

07:23.360 --> 07:24.440
-Yeah.
PAM: Sookie.

07:27.448 --> 07:30.155
I'm actually fucking happy to see you.

07:30.326 --> 07:31.611
TARA:
Back off, bitch.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.818
We made it, Sook.

07:35.914 --> 07:37.529
We made it.

07:44.256 --> 07:45.996
[TARA LAUGHS]

07:47.384 --> 07:49.841
Bill gave us his magical blood...

07:50.012 --> 07:52.298
...and now there's light.

07:52.473 --> 07:54.509
-I know.
-I know I'm still high...

07:54.683 --> 07:56.639
...but I swear I can never hate him again.

07:57.227 --> 07:59.479
Well, good luck with that.

07:59.647 --> 08:01.353
-Glad you made it home safe.
-Yeah.

08:03.942 --> 08:05.557
SOOKIE:
See you.

08:31.220 --> 08:32.960
There she is. Come on.

08:36.558 --> 08:37.593
It's beautiful.

08:37.768 --> 08:40.976
With 5500 years to prepare,
I should hope so.

08:42.481 --> 08:44.062
You know, even in ancient times...

08:44.233 --> 08:46.599
...the Maypole ceremony
was reserved only for fae...

08:46.777 --> 08:49.143
...who had found their soul mates.

08:49.321 --> 08:52.063
And that was rare, even then.
And the proof?

08:54.410 --> 08:56.492
If light shone from their touch.

08:58.622 --> 09:04.083
It's quite simple, when night falls,
you take this and I will take this.

09:04.628 --> 09:06.334
We wrap ourselves around the Maypole.

09:06.588 --> 09:09.671
Once we're fully entwined,
we use both our lights...

09:09.842 --> 09:12.754
...to render this one closed circle
into two...

09:12.928 --> 09:14.634
...and they become our wedding rings.

09:16.557 --> 09:19.139
-Warlow?
-Sookie?

09:19.309 --> 09:20.560
You know, I wasn't lying...

09:20.728 --> 09:23.515
-...when I said I keep my promises.
-Oh, I know.

09:23.731 --> 09:26.768
But a lot's changed since I last saw you.

09:27.943 --> 09:29.649
You've been gone four hours.

09:29.820 --> 09:31.811
It's not the amount of time.

09:31.989 --> 09:34.071
It's that | just watched
my friend get buried.

09:35.492 --> 09:37.448
Oh, Sookie...

09:38.078 --> 09:40.694
...do you know how many loved ones
I've seen buried?

09:40.873 --> 09:45.162
Please, just let me say this.

09:47.212 --> 09:48.713
All right.

09:49.757 --> 09:51.748
There's no denying
l have feelings for you.

09:52.217 --> 09:54.799
You've awakened something in me.

09:54.970 --> 09:58.428
But what has changed
is that my friends are safe...

09:58.599 --> 10:00.760
...and we're no longer in danger.

10:02.519 --> 10:03.929
So there's no ticking clock.

10:04.104 --> 10:07.596
So in other words,
I've held up my end of the bargain.

10:07.775 --> 10:09.185
You have...

10:09.359 --> 10:12.442
...but I'm thinking that a life
of eternity together...

10:12.613 --> 10:14.695
...should be based on more
than a bargain.

10:15.282 --> 10:17.273
[SIGHS]

10:17.993 --> 10:20.484
Okay, so, what do you suggest?

10:20.662 --> 10:22.072
-Honestly?
-Mm-hm.

10:23.707 --> 10:25.413
I'm asking if you'll date me.

10:27.461 --> 10:31.079
Date you?
As in drive-in movies and bowling?

10:32.007 --> 10:33.588
Not really, no.

10:33.759 --> 10:36.546
As in, we spend time
together off this plane...

10:36.720 --> 10:38.381
...in the real world,
see how we fit.

10:38.555 --> 10:40.136
-We made a deal, Sookie.
-I know...

10:40.307 --> 10:42.889
...but we don't need a closed circle
to be together.

10:43.060 --> 10:45.267
You could be part of this community.

10:45.437 --> 10:48.270
-They'l| accept you. My friends, family--
-Like Bill and Eric?

10:49.107 --> 10:51.063
Hmm? Who chained and drained me?

10:51.235 --> 10:53.692
No. Not them.

10:54.571 --> 10:56.402
I'm talking about Jason...

10:56.573 --> 10:59.656
...and Tara and Arlene.

11:01.620 --> 11:04.828
They still need me,
and I'm not ready to leave them behind.

11:11.880 --> 11:13.791
[SIGHS]

11:15.843 --> 11:17.208
[SOOKIE GROANS]

11:17.803 --> 11:22.422
Who the fuck do you think
you're talking to?

11:22.641 --> 11:24.222
[GASPING]

11:29.481 --> 11:30.766
[LAUGHING]

11:32.568 --> 11:34.684
Nice one, Jason. Whoo!

11:34.903 --> 11:38.145
Y'all might be vampires,
but I am an athlete.

11:42.744 --> 11:43.779
Whoo!

11:45.873 --> 11:47.409
JASON:
Let's go, Maverick.

11:50.085 --> 11:52.121
Hey, don't worry.
We'll get them next time.

11:53.088 --> 11:54.168
[GROANS]

11:56.383 --> 11:59.216
Sorry. Out of practice.

12:00.429 --> 12:01.509
You okay?

12:01.680 --> 12:03.591
-You almost killed her.
-Whoo!

12:03.807 --> 12:05.138
[BOTH LAUGHING]

12:05.851 --> 12:06.886
Heh.

12:09.062 --> 12:11.098
Okay.

12:19.072 --> 12:20.482
TARA:
Pam.

12:25.412 --> 12:27.949
-What's wrong?
-I think my buzz wore off.

12:28.123 --> 12:30.284
Don't tell me with the sun
shining above you...

12:30.459 --> 12:32.040
...and after the shit
we went through...

12:32.210 --> 12:35.247
-...you're sitting here brooding over Eric.
-Has Willa realized Eric's gone?

12:35.422 --> 12:36.787
I don't think so.

12:37.716 --> 12:38.751
Why?

12:40.802 --> 12:42.508
You're going to be pissed.

12:42.971 --> 12:45.633
Don't even tell me
you're thinking of going after him.

12:48.268 --> 12:49.724
You gotta be
fucking kidding me!

12:50.562 --> 12:52.894
Don't even start with that shit, Tara...

12:53.065 --> 12:54.976
...because I don't want to...

12:55.692 --> 12:58.604
...but I will release you
if you push me.

13:03.575 --> 13:04.781
Take care of Willa?

13:06.703 --> 13:09.570
You guys are the worst
fucking makers ever.

13:28.934 --> 13:31.971
Hey, don't you want to come outside?

13:35.607 --> 13:37.108
What is it?

13:39.569 --> 13:43.153
All the blood that I lost,
it seems that my abilities have gone.

13:46.868 --> 13:48.779
Maybe you're just healing.

13:49.871 --> 13:51.372
I'm healed, Jess.

13:52.499 --> 13:54.956
I don't feel Lilith anymore.
I feel like Bill again.

13:57.587 --> 13:59.794
You say that like it's a bad thing.

14:01.425 --> 14:03.586
I suppose it's not, but....

14:06.888 --> 14:08.094
What?

14:09.891 --> 14:11.392
SooHe.

14:16.690 --> 14:18.351
What about Sookie?

14:18.525 --> 14:19.981
This blood...

14:21.903 --> 14:25.066
...that's allowing you
to walk around in the daylight...

14:27.034 --> 14:28.274
...it came at a price.

14:29.202 --> 14:31.318
There's a vampire-fae hybrid...

14:31.496 --> 14:33.748
...and he wanted Sookie.

14:34.291 --> 14:36.577
And I knew I needed to save you...

14:39.671 --> 14:43.038
...so in exchange for his blood,
I sacrificed her.

14:45.510 --> 14:47.296
She's going to be made vampire.

14:48.513 --> 14:50.504
-When?
-lmminently.

14:51.308 --> 14:53.594
Then what the hell
are you doing sitting here?

14:55.520 --> 14:57.476
There's nothing I can do now.

14:57.647 --> 14:59.683
Bill-- Bill, we're saved.

14:59.858 --> 15:03.271
-It worked. Now go. Go get her.
-All the pain that I caused her.

15:03.779 --> 15:05.440
There's no coming back from it now.

15:07.783 --> 15:09.694
-You said you were Bill again.
-I am.

15:09.868 --> 15:12.575
Bill Compton would've walked
through fire to save her life.

15:13.038 --> 15:15.154
-There's no time now.
-Bullshit!

15:15.582 --> 15:17.698
Yeah, maybe you were an asshole...

15:18.043 --> 15:20.876
...but right now you have the opportunity
to make this right.

15:22.464 --> 15:24.546
At the beginning of all of this...

15:25.217 --> 15:28.175
...you said that I had to protect
your humanity.

15:29.596 --> 15:32.429
Please do not make a failure out of me.

15:43.318 --> 15:44.558
Where's Jason?

15:45.445 --> 15:46.901
Warlow.

15:47.405 --> 15:51.398
That motherfucker killed my parents.

15:51.618 --> 15:56.829
There's no way Sookie would agree
to be his goddamn fairy vampire bride.

15:59.709 --> 16:01.745
What the fuck did you do?

16:02.546 --> 16:04.036
l encouraged her.

16:04.589 --> 16:06.500
I may very well kill you...

16:06.716 --> 16:08.707
...Bill Compton, God...

16:08.885 --> 16:10.341
...whatever the fuck you are!

16:10.512 --> 16:11.627
-Jason.
-Jason.

16:15.559 --> 16:18.266
But right now I need to save my sister.

16:19.896 --> 16:22.103
So how do I do that?

16:22.274 --> 16:25.437
They're on another plane,
a fairy plane.

16:25.610 --> 16:27.942
-What?
BlLL: It can only be accessed through a portal...

16:28.113 --> 16:30.274
...in the cemetery using a fae's light.

16:31.741 --> 16:34.403
The only other fae in Bon Temps
is Andy's daughter Adilyn.

16:34.578 --> 16:35.909
Oh, God.

16:36.079 --> 16:38.161
We have to go to Andy
and ask for her assistance.

16:38.331 --> 16:39.616
JESSICA:
We can't.

16:40.125 --> 16:42.992
Andy will never give Jason
what he needs if we do.

16:43.211 --> 16:45.167
-|'|| go alone.
VIOLET: No, you won't.

16:46.923 --> 16:49.209
You'll never be alone again.

16:51.011 --> 16:52.922
Yeah, let's roll.

16:56.433 --> 16:59.266
-Where are you taking me?
-Keep moving.

16:59.477 --> 17:01.058
[TAKAHASHI WHIMPERING]

17:04.691 --> 17:05.976
You drank the blood.

17:06.151 --> 17:10.110
-lt's not my fault I failed to synthesize--
-I know this, Takahashi. Keep walking.

17:14.701 --> 17:16.441
Now stop.

17:17.245 --> 17:18.746
This is where we part ways.

17:18.914 --> 17:21.621
Please, I have a wife.

17:21.791 --> 17:22.826
l have children.

17:24.211 --> 17:25.792
Don't hurt me. I beg you.

17:26.379 --> 17:27.459
Please!

17:27.631 --> 17:29.167
Look in my eyes.

17:32.719 --> 17:34.334
You never met me.

17:35.639 --> 17:36.970
Or Jessica.

17:37.974 --> 17:40.681
Or any of the other creatures
you came into contact with...

17:40.852 --> 17:43.434
...in the last couple of weeks.
Do you understand?

17:43.605 --> 17:44.936
Yes.

17:45.106 --> 17:46.892
In a moment I will leave.

17:47.067 --> 17:49.729
The bag that I placed at your feet,
you will take it home.

17:50.695 --> 17:52.401
I hope your wife and your children...

17:52.572 --> 17:55.439
...find it within their hearts
to forgive you for your absence.

17:56.034 --> 17:59.367
I'm sorry for the pain that I caused them,
but this I cannot take away.

18:02.123 --> 18:04.830
Goodbye, Hido Takahashi.

18:19.474 --> 18:20.429
[IN JAPANESE]

18:20.600 --> 18:22.591
Holy shit...

18:27.148 --> 18:29.184
-Now, let me talk.
-Mm-hm.

18:29.693 --> 18:31.775
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

18:33.488 --> 18:35.695
ANDY: All right, already.
JASON: Oh, hi.

18:35.907 --> 18:39.149
Stackhouse, where the hell you been?

18:39.703 --> 18:42.285
-Hello.
-This here's Violet.

18:42.455 --> 18:44.411
Where I been, it's a long story.

18:44.916 --> 18:47.293
lnvite us in? I'll explain.

18:47.502 --> 18:49.038
Don't gotta stand on ceremony.

18:50.880 --> 18:53.963
-You need to invite me in.
-Oh, hell, no.

18:54.134 --> 18:57.467
-Holly, get Adilyn upstairs!
VIOLET: I'm 800 years old...

18:57.679 --> 19:01.422
...and your halfling daughter does smell good,
but I only feed on Jason.

19:01.599 --> 19:03.180
We're strictly monogamous.

19:03.393 --> 19:05.179
That's some bullshit right there.

19:05.353 --> 19:08.015
-Go, go, go.
-Wait! Andy, we need Adilyn to save Sookie.

19:08.189 --> 19:09.349
SooHe?

19:10.525 --> 19:11.856
Hey there, Adilyn.

19:12.027 --> 19:14.518
My name is Officer Jason Stackhouse.

19:14.696 --> 19:15.776
| work with your daddy.

19:16.531 --> 19:17.611
I want you to know...

19:18.199 --> 19:21.236
...I know what happened
with you and your sisters...

19:21.411 --> 19:22.446
...and I'm real sorry.

19:22.620 --> 19:25.453
But my sister Sookie,
she's been through a lot too.

19:25.623 --> 19:28.911
-Don't listen to him, Adilyn.
-And just like you, she don't deserve it.

19:29.085 --> 19:32.077
Goddamn it, Stackhouse.
I want you to leave.

19:32.547 --> 19:35.163
IASON: I can ’t lose my sister
like you lost all yours.

19:35.342 --> 19:36.752
Please.

19:36.926 --> 19:38.917
Adilyn, honey, come upstairs with me.

19:39.095 --> 19:41.757
-How can I help?
-We need you to come with us.

19:42.182 --> 19:44.798
Okay? To the cemetery.
That's where Sookie is.

19:44.976 --> 19:47.012
Except she's on a-- A different--

19:47.187 --> 19:48.302
-Plane.
-Yeah.

19:48.480 --> 19:53.270
-With some fairy vampire murderous fuck.
-Jesus.

19:53.443 --> 19:54.478
JASON:
I'm sorry.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.731
But, Andy, this is the same murderous fuck
who killed my folks.

19:57.947 --> 20:00.859
So we need Adilyn's light
to get us onto that plane...

20:01.493 --> 20:03.575
...or else he's gonna take Sookie
from me too.

20:05.372 --> 20:06.703
I'm sorry, Stackhouse.

20:06.873 --> 20:08.829
I can't put my daughter
back in harm's way.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.285
Daddy.

20:10.585 --> 20:11.620
I wanna do this.

20:14.089 --> 20:16.580
Sookie's the only other girl like me I know.

20:16.800 --> 20:21.134
And I couldn't save
Braelyn or Charlaine or Danika...

20:22.639 --> 20:24.755
...but maybe if I could help save her....

20:34.526 --> 20:36.812
-Let's do this shit, then.
-Mm-hm.

20:37.862 --> 20:39.022
But we're going in heavy.

20:39.197 --> 20:40.937
Hey, there ain't no other way.

20:42.450 --> 20:44.281
JASON:
You can never have too much.

20:55.755 --> 20:57.040
Come on, Andy, let's go.

20:57.215 --> 20:58.580
Let's rock 'n' roll.

21:01.803 --> 21:03.543
WARLOW:
That'll hold you.

21:05.682 --> 21:08.674
Do you think I've waited 5500 years...

21:08.852 --> 21:10.638
...to become a part of your community?

21:12.522 --> 21:15.559
To share you with your friends of low birth...

21:15.733 --> 21:17.394
