40:35.642 --> 40:37.178
Amen!

40:37.352 --> 40:39.138
What's the catch?

40:39.354 --> 40:41.265
Because ain't nothing in life for free.

40:41.481 --> 40:42.857
WOMAN:
That's true.

40:43.025 --> 40:44.185
You're a smart woman.

40:44.943 --> 40:46.319
Thank you.

40:46.486 --> 40:48.022
SAM:
Yes, there is a catch.

40:48.196 --> 40:51.359
But the catch is for your safety.

40:52.701 --> 40:54.407
For everybody's safety.

40:54.578 --> 40:56.068
Now...

40:57.581 --> 40:59.117
...I am asking...

40:59.291 --> 41:03.751
...every single uninfected adult
in this room...

41:04.379 --> 41:08.497
...to agree to a monogamous
feeding relationship...

41:08.675 --> 41:10.131
...with a healthy vampire...

41:10.302 --> 41:11.633
...in exchange--

41:11.845 --> 41:13.130
[CROWD CLAMORING]

41:13.347 --> 41:15.212
In exchange for that
healthy vampire's protection...

41:15.390 --> 41:16.846
...for you and your children.

41:17.017 --> 41:19.759
Listen, I understand you're upset.

41:19.936 --> 41:21.096
Talk to your reverends.

41:21.647 --> 41:23.057
Talk amongst yourselves.

41:23.273 --> 41:25.650
But this is the only way
we know how to protect you.

41:25.817 --> 41:29.059
Now, if we're gonna be safe,
every single human needs a vampire...

41:29.237 --> 41:30.852
...and every vampire needs a human.

41:31.615 --> 41:34.322
Now, I hope I'm gonna see
all y'all tonight.

41:35.786 --> 41:37.617
If I don't...

41:39.998 --> 41:41.954
...God be with you.

41:43.710 --> 41:45.575
[BAND PLAYING ROCK MUSIC]

41:52.344 --> 41:54.005
[SINGING]

41:56.014 --> 41:57.879
WOMAN:
That's nice!

41:58.100 --> 41:59.340
[ALL APPLAUDING]

42:04.731 --> 42:06.141
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

42:12.114 --> 42:15.447
-I'm sure to protect you.
MAN: Hey! Come here.

42:15.617 --> 42:17.323
Stop!

42:17.494 --> 42:18.950
Stop. What are you doing?

42:19.162 --> 42:20.197
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

42:57.284 --> 42:58.490
Negative. You?

42:59.161 --> 43:00.196
All good.

43:01.913 --> 43:03.904
ALCIDE: Jesus Christ.
-Let's leave Jesus out of it.

43:04.082 --> 43:06.368
I don't think he's got
anything to do with this.

43:06.710 --> 43:09.076
The way they made it sound
at church this morning...

43:09.254 --> 43:12.963
-...you'd think he was catering the thing.
ARLENE: Listen up, everyone.

43:13.133 --> 43:16.170
Come, all my children, eat.

43:16.344 --> 43:19.051
No, no, that would be Arlene.

43:21.349 --> 43:22.384
One hour.

43:23.018 --> 43:24.098
One hour.

43:24.269 --> 43:26.885
We'll just say our hellos,
make sure we're seen...

43:27.063 --> 43:29.975
...eat some barbecue,
and that's it, all right?

43:30.150 --> 43:31.686
All right, let's do this.

43:35.447 --> 43:38.439
-So you seen anyone you might wanna--?
-Mm-mm.

43:38.617 --> 43:40.107
| used to hate vegetarians.

43:40.619 --> 43:43.736
Now I'd do just about anything
to find one.

43:44.206 --> 43:46.367
[BOTH LAUGHING]

43:46.792 --> 43:48.532
LETTIE MAE:
Tara?

43:51.546 --> 43:53.923
l was wondering
if you and me could talk.

44:04.351 --> 44:05.511
|'m-- I'm Willa.

44:05.811 --> 44:08.177
Lettie Mae Daniels. I'm Tara's mother.

44:08.980 --> 44:11.141
Oh, well, it's nice to meet you.

44:12.609 --> 44:15.442
You and Tara, you're friends?

44:16.196 --> 44:19.279
Yes, we are friends.

44:21.284 --> 44:23.445
Tell her to talk to me.

44:31.002 --> 44:32.663
What the fuck you want?

44:32.838 --> 44:35.796
To apologize for the way
I handled things.

44:36.800 --> 44:38.586
You talking about
when you came to Fangtasia?

44:38.760 --> 44:41.376
I'm talking about everything, Tara.

44:41.555 --> 44:43.637
I'm talking about your whole life.

44:45.016 --> 44:50.352
I am so terribly sorry.

44:53.650 --> 44:55.857
I don't know what to say.

44:56.027 --> 44:58.018
Just listen, then.

44:59.030 --> 45:01.021
When your father left...

45:02.659 --> 45:06.026
...I loved him
with everything I had in me...

45:07.289 --> 45:11.623
...and I hurt for myself.

45:12.586 --> 45:14.918
So much so...

45:15.088 --> 45:17.454
...I forgot to hurt for you.

45:18.300 --> 45:21.167
There were even times
when | forgot to--

45:22.012 --> 45:24.549
Lord have mercy on my soul.

45:24.764 --> 45:26.800
It's okay, Mama.

45:26.975 --> 45:30.809
-You don't have to do this.
-Oh, yes, I do.

45:32.814 --> 45:34.554
| forgot to feed you, Tara.

45:36.818 --> 45:40.231
For days at a time, I would forget.

45:41.031 --> 45:42.146
I made do.

45:42.324 --> 45:43.609
No, you didn't.

45:43.825 --> 45:46.737
It was my job to feed you...

45:47.412 --> 45:49.573
...and I didn't do it.

45:50.040 --> 45:51.871
I thought--

45:52.709 --> 45:57.453
I thought I never could forgive myself...

45:57.631 --> 45:59.667
...but if you let me, Tara...

45:59.841 --> 46:04.050
...I can make this right
for the both of us.

46:04.220 --> 46:07.348
Come here. Let me feed you.

46:12.312 --> 46:15.054
-I can't.
-Please.

46:16.107 --> 46:20.601
This whole thing,
all the trouble in this world...

46:20.779 --> 46:22.610
...it's a blessing, Tara.

46:22.781 --> 46:24.612
It's a chance for us to heal.

46:28.912 --> 46:30.368
Come here.

46:31.289 --> 46:33.280
Let me feed you.

46:33.458 --> 46:34.789
Let me take care of you.

46:35.710 --> 46:39.373
Let me nourish my baby girl.

46:57.607 --> 46:59.984
WOMAN [ON TV]: The winner of the pageant
should be an all-around little girl...

47:00.151 --> 47:02.767
...who's having a great time,
who's comfortable in herself...

47:02.946 --> 47:05.187
...loves being on stage
and feels conﬁdent and that's really it.

47:05.407 --> 47:06.442
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

47:06.658 --> 47:08.148
WOMAN:
We are starting the pageant.

47:08.326 --> 47:10.738
-|'|| get it.
-Okay, Daddy.

47:22.007 --> 47:23.497
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

47:36.062 --> 47:37.177
You didn't come tonight.

47:38.356 --> 47:41.223
No, you murdering piece of shit, I did not.

47:41.401 --> 47:44.359
-Daddy, who is it?
-Stay where you are, sweetheart.

47:45.447 --> 47:47.654
I came to offer you protection...

47:47.824 --> 47:49.485
...for both of you.

47:51.036 --> 47:54.995
You got some nerve asking for any more
of this family's blood.

47:55.540 --> 47:57.076
I'm not asking for your blood.

47:57.375 --> 47:59.161
Then what the fuck do you want?

48:01.671 --> 48:03.536
I want to give you your girls back...

48:05.341 --> 48:06.672
...but I can't.

48:06.843 --> 48:08.879
The only thing that I can give you now...

48:09.054 --> 48:13.593
...is some kind of peace of mind
that you and Adilyn will be safe.

48:16.061 --> 48:18.222
That you'll never have to worry.

48:20.148 --> 48:21.388
You have my word.

48:23.651 --> 48:25.778
What if I don't want it?

48:26.821 --> 48:28.686
You've got it anyway.

49:19.374 --> 49:21.114
[BAND PLAYING ROCK MUSIC]

49:28.758 --> 49:30.464
BILL:
Leaving so soon?

49:32.053 --> 49:33.964
ALCIDE: Bill.
-Alcide.

49:34.806 --> 49:36.842
I saw you on TV last night.

49:37.016 --> 49:39.098
You-- You were good.

49:44.232 --> 49:46.063
May l have a moment alone with Sookie?

49:46.484 --> 49:48.896
-No fucking way.
-Honey, it's fine.

49:49.070 --> 49:50.355
No, it ain't, Sookie.

49:50.530 --> 49:53.613
Anything Bill has to say to you,
he can say to me too.

49:54.826 --> 49:56.441
You heard the man.

49:58.121 --> 49:59.657
You meet anyone tonight?

49:59.831 --> 50:01.742
If you're asking
if I made arrangements...

50:01.916 --> 50:04.658
...with any vampires, Bill,
no, I did not.

50:04.836 --> 50:07.248
But I did meet some lovely people.

50:07.422 --> 50:09.708
You need a vampire in your life, Sookie.

50:10.550 --> 50:12.381
More so than anyone else here.

50:13.595 --> 50:15.210
You need protection.

50:15.388 --> 50:17.504
-She's got me.
-You're not good enough.

50:17.724 --> 50:20.807
-Grr.
-You can growl all you want, bright eyes...

50:20.977 --> 50:23.013
...but it doesn't change the truth.

50:26.399 --> 50:27.935
I'm offering you my protection.

50:28.109 --> 50:29.565
And I appreciate that...

50:29.736 --> 50:33.320
...but I'm gonna take my chances
all the same.

50:35.617 --> 50:37.699
I've changed, Sookie.

50:37.869 --> 50:39.450
I can be trusted again.

50:40.121 --> 50:42.453
That's the thing, though.
Even at your best...

50:44.417 --> 50:47.079
...I could never really trust you.

50:47.503 --> 50:48.538
[SNIFFING]

50:48.755 --> 50:50.211
-You smell that?
-Smel| what?

50:50.381 --> 50:52.417
| smell it.

50:52.759 --> 50:55.045
Somebody mind telling me
what the hell's going on?

51:05.271 --> 51:07.011
[SNARLING]
